{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01HyR9g33uMuunzNTtqFkFoF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01CTdyPhhx3BDmpY3i4WFqSj","name":"mcp__planflow-mcp__planflow_remember","input":{"title":"Live gallery client store (T3.3)","content":"src/lib/gallery.ts is a framework-agnostic Svelte store (classic writable, not runes) because vitest runs in the `node` environment — keeping it rune-free makes the seed/merge/reconnect logic unit-testable without the Svelte compiler. createGalleryStore() injects fetch, a WebSocket factory, and the photos/ws URLs so tests drive a FakeSocket. It seeds from GET /api/photos, opens /api/ws, and merges the { type:'photo:new', photo } envelope via mergePhoto (prepend newest-first, dedupe by id so a client never sees its own upload twice). Socket auto-reconnects with exponential backoff; a failed seed is non-fatal (still goes live). Gallery.svelte renders a CSS-columns masonry with a scale/fade `in:` transition — Svelte skips intros on the initial render, so only live-prepended items animate.","type":"decision","projectId":"009df0ac-fd92-45a4-9377-32fe07e9d561"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":845,"cache_read_input_tokens":68872,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":845},"output_tokens":49,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b993d51d-2ee5-4324-86da-92972366a562","uuid":"568a9434-a266-4782-aa3c-6f8a09fefdd9","request_id":"req_011CbRS2SXRxvt7A5Np6fm3m"}
