{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01LhpqXKvzwzsbr9FGd96fJ3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"T3.3 complete and merged into master. ✅\n\n## Summary\n\nBuilt the live gallery client per the T3.3 contract:\n\n**`src/lib/gallery.ts`** — a framework-agnostic Svelte store (classic `writable`, not runes, so it's unit-testable in vitest's `node` env). `createGalleryStore()`:\n- Seeds from `GET /api/photos`\n- Opens a WebSocket to `/api/ws` and merges `{ type: 'photo:new', photo }` envelopes\n- `mergePhoto` prepends newest-first and **dedupes by id** (a client never sees its own upload twice)\n- Auto-reconnects with exponential backoff; a failed seed is non-fatal (still goes live)\n- Injectable `fetch` / `WebSocket` / URLs for testing\n\n**`src/lib/components/Gallery.svelte`** — responsive CSS-columns masonry, lazy-loaded images, with a `scale`/fade `in:` transition. Svelte skips intros on the initial render, so seeded photos appear instantly and only **live-prepended** items animate.\n\n**`src/routes/+page.svelte`** — creates the store, `start()`s on mount, `destroy()`s on unmount.\n\n**Tests** — 10 new unit tests (merge / parse / seed / reconnect / destroy) using a `FakeSocket`; full suite 68/68 passing.\n\n### Validation\n- `npm run check` — 0 errors (lone warning is a pre-existing tsconfig `node`-types issue, unrelated)\n- `npm test` — 68 passed\n- `npm run build` — green (Cloudflare adapter)\n\n### Delivery\nA stray commit landed on the T3.2 branch first; I created the T3.3 branch off `origin/master` (which already has T3.2 via squash-merge #7), cherry-picked the commit for a clean 4-file diff, and reset the T3.2 branch. PR **#8** opened against `master`, auto-merge enabled, **merged** as `e49a0db`. Task marked DONE in PlanFlow.\n\n**Cleanup note:** this ran in-place in the main checkout. The dispatcher can drop the working-tree entry if desired with `planflow_worktree_remove(taskId: \"T3.3\")`."}],"s